Package de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.junit

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CombinatorialTestExecutionCallback
    Used to call the ExecutionReporter.testInputExecutionStarted(Combination) and ExecutionReporter.testInputExecutionFinished(Combination, TestResult) method for registered reporters and generate new test inputs based on test results (for example for fault characterization).
    CombinatorialTestExtension
    The extension handling a CombinatorialTest.
    CombinatorialTestInvocationContext
    Handles one test input in a combinatorial test and the extensions needed for one test input: CombinatorialTestParameterResolver and CombinatorialTestExecutionCallback.
    CombinatorialTestMethodContext
    One context for a complete CombinatorialTest.
    CombinatorialTestNameFormatter
    Formats the name of one test input in a CombinatorialTest according to the name defined in CombinatorialTest.name(), the currently tested Combination, and the test index.
    CombinatorialTestParameterResolver
    Handles parameter resolving for parameters in test inputs from a CombinatorialTest.
    TestInputIterator
    A special Iterator since streaming a java Queue directly does not allow concurrent modification of said queue.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    CombinatorialTest
    This annotation is used to mark a method which is a combinatorial test.
